[Note the 2 cases described above were unvaccinated and not listed as contacts. Herein lies one of the major problems in controlling Ebola. If only known contacts are vaccinated (rather than a village) and furthermore, if patients go to traditional doctors, the virus will continue to spread. It is a very difficult situation requiring education and cooperation of the villagers. - Mod.LK]

- Thu 17 Oct 2019. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
