The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 16 Oct 2019:

-Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3228, of which 3144 are confirmed and 114 are probable. In total, there were 2158 deaths (2044 confirmed and 114 probable) and 1038 people healed.
- 443 suspected cases under investigation;
- 1 new confirmed case in North Kivu, including 1 case in North Kivu in Mabalako and no cases in Ituri;
- 4 new confirmed deaths in North Kivu, including 1 community death in North Kivu in Mabalako and 3 deaths confirmed at the CTE in North Kivu in Mabalako;
- No healed person left CTE;
- No health workers are among the newly confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed / probable cases among health workers is 161 (5% of all confirmed / probable cases), including 41 deaths.

Vaccination
-----------
- A satellite ring was opened in Mambasa prison around the confirmed case of 12 Oct 2019 in Nyakunde;
- Continuation of expanded ring vaccination in Mataba in the health zone of Kalunguta around the 2 confirmed cases of 12 Oct 2019;
- Continuation of the vaccination of newly recruited front-line staff (PPL) in the Kyondo (HGR Kyondo) and Kayna health zones (Bulinda health area), Musienene (Kimbulu Reference Health Center), and Butembo (Vulindi health area);
- Preparation of the vaccination of biker taximen in the sub-coordinations of Butembo, Beni, Mangina in Mabalako in North Kivu, and Mambasa in Ituri.
- Since the beginning of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 239 139 people have been vaccinated;
- The only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 20 May 2018.

Monitoring at entry points
---------------------
- Nasty destruction of huts and launching leaflets against providers at PoC Kolikoko;
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the total number of checked travelers (temperature rise) at the sanitary control points is 106 999 606;
- To date, a total of 111 entry points (PoE) and sanitary control points (PoCs) have been set up in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri to protect the country's major cities and prevent the spread of the epidemic in neighboring countries.

